JOHANNESBURG – Zimbabwe Cricket (ZC) on Sunday confirmed the resignation of Makhaya Ntini as bowling coach of the national team. Ntini, 40, played 101 Tests for South Africa, had been in charge of the Zimbabwe cricket team since his appointment in February 2016. ZC made the announcement on Sunday afternoon. “ZC regrets to announce that Makhaya Ntini, the national team bowling coach, has tendered his resignation, with immediate effect. “And while reluctantly accepting his resignation, ZC fully appreciates and respects his decision, and wishes him all the best for the future.”  African News Agency